  visitorName: Alex Wood
  birthYear: 1972
  birthMonth: 1
  birthDay: 4
  personality: Very talkative
  genuineGreeting: "open up this damn gate \u2018fore I tear it off it\u2019s hinges."
  mimicGreeting: "open up this damn gate \u2018fore I tear it off it\u2019s hinges."
  genuineClosing: "Oh and I\u2019m be billing for the time it took \u2018ya to let
    me out."
  mimicClosing: "Oh and I\u2019m be billing for the time it took \u2018ya to let
    me out."
  genuineRejected: My legal representative in the Department of Labor will be hearing
    about this.
  mimicRejected: My legal representative in the Department of Labor will be hearing
    about this.
  genuineNameResponse: 'All my friends just call me Al, or Alex, or Alan wrench,
    or Al Might, or Alcatraz, or Alakazam

    Al-catraz al-akabam. But you, you
    my friend, can call me Wood.'
  genuineBirthdayResponse: 1972 January 4th
  genuineReasonResponse: "So I clock into work today and boss Says HEY ALEX and I
    was like yeah Mike? Park says they want you down at 9pm to fix the generator.
    And I was like what happened to the fix I did last week. And he says yeah well
    it broke again. \nAnd I said I bet the power cables just loose again, did ya
    tell them to check the power cable? And he say\u2019s yeah said they did and
    it\u2019s not that. So I say son of a b***h and I leave at 8 to fix the generator.
    \u2018Course then my car breaks down\nsince the radiator overheats so I have
    to wait in the shade till half past noon for it to cool down so I can continue
    up the path. Anyways, I roll up and Layla at the gate is looking dazzlin\u2019
    if ya know what I\u2019m saying. An\u2019 of course the cable has\ncome loose
    again LIKE I SAID IT WAS. So I just plug \u2018er in, give it a good kick and
    it\u2019s good as new. \u2018Course then I try to leave and THE DAMN DOOR\u2019S
    STUCK and there I am stuck banging on the door for the next three or four hours
    before that \nsenile old crone McGuffers finally comes to the shed to get some
    batteries for his dead hearing aids"
  genuineTimeResponse: 1:27 but for billing reasons I entered at 1.
  mimicNameResponse: 'All my friends just call me Al, or Alex, or Alan wrench, or
    Al Might, or Alcatraz, or Alakazam

    Al-catraz al-akabam. But you, you my
